            "content_html": "<img src=\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/29818440?u=3d5719046fc2b935d980258fed433232b61cb7ed&v=4\" width=\"64\" height=\"64\" alt=\"\"/><br/><h2 dir=\"auto\">Description of changes</h2>\n<p dir=\"auto\">Previously if the user enables this module but doesn't use the battery feature, the user can't enable upower (at least without lib.mkForce).</p>\n<p dir=\"auto\">Minimal config to reproduce the issue this PR solves:</p>\n<div class=\"highlight highlight-source-nix notranslate position-relative overflow-auto\" dir=\"auto\" data-snippet-clipboard-copy-content=\"services.upower.enable = true;\nservices.dwm-status.enable = true;\nservices.dwm-status.order = [ ];\"><pre class=\"notranslate\"><span class=\"pl-s1\">services</span><span class=\"pl-kos\">.</span><span class=\"pl-c1\"><span class=\"pl-c1\">upower</span><span class=\"pl-kos\">.</span><span class=\"pl-en\">enable</span></span> <span class=\"pl-kos\">=</span> <span class=\"pl-smi\">true</span><span class=\"pl-kos\">;</span>\n<span class=\"pl-s1\">services</span><span class=\"pl-kos\">.</span><span class=\"pl-c1\"><span class=\"pl-c1\">dwm-status</span><span class=\"pl-kos\">.</span><span class=\"pl-c1\">enable</span></span> <span class=\"pl-kos\">=</span> <span class=\"pl-smi\">true</span><span class=\"pl-kos\">;</span>\n<span class=\"pl-s1\">services</span><span class=\"pl-kos\">.</span><span class=\"pl-c1\"><span class=\"pl-c1\">dwm-status</span><span class=\"pl-kos\">.</span><span class=\"pl-c1\">order</span></span> <span class=\"pl-kos\">=</span> <span class=\"pl-kos\">[</span> <span class=\"pl-kos\">]</span><span class=\"pl-kos\">;</span></pre></div>\n<div class=\"snippet-clipboard-content notranslate position-relative overflow-auto\" data-snippet-clipboard-copy-content=\"error: The option `services.upower.enable' has conflicting definition values:\n- In `/nix/store/fz9xjls44cx9aqh16cw2j9li5jpzn8ky-source/system.nix': true\n- In `/nix/store/wcidiyklj0nrljlz5m3qlkvhv8f2d